Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Exercises 5x week
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Women's Health Recommendations:

Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day.
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Limit animal fat intake in diet
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: High uric acid may cause gout and has been associated with risk of heart disease, foods which can aggravate gout are red meat and alcohol.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Overview Notes: To manage inflammation and help with cholesterol levels take 2- 4g of omega 3 supplements a day
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: To manage inflammation and help with cholesterol levels take 2- 4g of omega 3 supplements a day

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: 0
Comment Key: ClinicalExamNote
Comment Value: Slight hyperinflation on chest exam. Hearing in left ear abnormal for low frequencies.
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Overview Notes: Limit your intake of sweet things, refined carbs and sugar in tea to manage diabetes risk.
Comment Key: CurrentComplaintRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: High uric acid may cause gout and has been associated with risk of heart disease, foods which can aggravate gout are red meat and alcohol.
Comment Key: EyesightRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Overview Notes: High uric acid may cause gout and has been associated with risk of heart disease, foods which can aggravate gout are red meat and alcohol.
Comment Key: LabTestRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations:

2) High uric acid
3) Slightly high homocysteine
4) High CRP (inflammation)
5) Mother has Diabetes

Comment Key: LifestyleRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Men's Health Recommendations: Please review any new urinary difficulties with your doctor.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: High uric acid may cause gout and has been associated with risk of heart disease, foods which can aggravate gout are red meat and alcohol.

Overview Notes: 1) Slightly high LDL (bad cholesterol)
2) High uric acid
3) Slightly high homocysteine
4) High CRP (inflammation)
5) Mother has Diabetes

Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Overview Notes: High uric acid may cause gout and has been associated with risk of heart disease, foods which can aggravate gout are red meat and alcohol.
Comment Key: ReportRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: To manage inflammation and help with cholesterol levels take 2- 4g of omega 3 supplements a day
Comment Key: SpecialInvestigationRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Overview Notes: High uric acid may cause gout and has been associated with risk of heart disease, foods which can aggravate gout are red meat and alcohol.
Comment Key: SymptomScreeningNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: To manage inflammation and help with cholesterol levels take 2- 4g of omega 3 supplements a day
Comment Key: SymptomScreeningRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Overview Notes: You can reduce your homocysteine level with a good B vitamin supplement (Solal homocysteine lowering formula)
Comment Key: SymptomScreeningRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Generally in good health on the day of examination.
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Limit your intake of sweet things, refined carbs and sugar in tea to manage diabetes risk.

Nurse: Lebo Cindi

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Limit your intake of sweet things, refined carbs and sugar in tea to manage diabetes risk.

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Exercises 5x week
Comment Key: VitalsRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: High uric acid may cause gout and has been associated with risk of heart disease, foods which can aggravate gout are red meat and alcohol.
Comment Key: VitaminsOrSupplements
Comment Value: Multivitamin , omega
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: To manage inflammation and help with cholesterol levels take 2- 4g of omega 3 supplements a day
Comment Key: WomensHealthRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: FEV1 was 70 % which is consistent with history of asthma. To compare with old reports when available.
